title: "My Internship Journey"
author: Ritika Verma
vinternship_id: WIN251550

When I started my Internship at VLED Labs , I was both excited and scared.
In the beginning even small things felt difficult. Sometimes I had to read the same question multiple times to understand it. 
There were moments when i felt stuck and frustrated. But slowly, I started learning how to handle this feeling.
The case studies at VLED Labs are truly helpful.They help us understand concepts through real world scenarios,which makes learning more practical.

 I understood that struggling with a problem is not a sign of weakness instead it's a part of learning.
 It taught me patience. It taught me consistency.I realized that it's okay not to know everything. What matters is the willingness to learn.

Thanks to Sudarshan Iyengar sir for reminding us that 'With consistency,even the impossible starts to feel possible.
' I'm grateful for this experience. It helped me grow not just as a student,but as a person.

